GRAND RAPIDS , MI - City High Middle school has been ranked the 21 st most challenging high school in the Midwest by the Washington Post , Grand Rapids Public Schools leaders announced Monday , May 19 .
Grand River Preparatory High School , a Kentwood charter school , placed sixth out of the 257 Midwest schools rated .
Only 2,063 schools out of over 20,000 U.S. public High schools earned placement on the Post 's 2014 National High School Challenge Index .
